fields.physical_description:
Album, cabinet prints, photographic cards, cartes, and prints.
1. 28-page album with metal-clasped dark green leatherette-bound
boards, the front tooled & gilt with a spray of lillies in art nouveau style; some pages are colour-printed with sprays of flowers & all have
gilt-edged apertures for the photographs.  1890-1910; 27.2 x 21.3 cm
2. sepia photographic print (portrait proportions) in beige mount: a boy seated in a chair & a younger girl standing on his left: he in a tailored coat & cap, breeches & button boots; she in a double-breasted fur coat & fur-trimmed hat.  1890-1910; approx. 16.5 x 10.8 cm
3. sepia cabinet print of a young woman.  Print 16.4 x 10.7 cm
4. sepia cabinet print of a man in uniform.  Print 16.5 x 10.6 cm
5. sepia photographic print of three men & two women. 16.4 x 10.8 cm
6. sepia photographic print (portrait proportions) in a white card mount: a little girl in fancy dress/stage costume, standing in a garden & wearing a light-coloured yoked party dress with matching shoes & stockings, & a cap with a star at the front; she carries a wand topped with a crescent moon.  1890-1910; image 7.9 x 5.2 cm
7. sepia cabinet print (portrait proportions) by Graham of Leamington Spa, showing a young man seated in a chair, with a small fair-haired
child on his left knee: the child wears a lace-trimmed pinafore & dress with socks & button-boots.  1880-1900; image 14.5 x 10 cm
8. sepia cabinet print (portrait proportions) by the London & Coventry
Photo Co of Coventry: a young child kneeling on a chair beside a baby
propped on a rug-covered chair: the child has blonde curls & wears a
white dress with a tartan sash; the baby is bare-footed & wears a tucked dress.  1870-1890; image 13.4 x 9.1 cm
9. sepia photographic postcard (landscape proportions), showing a line
of nine girls dressed in pierrot-style costumes: the tallest wears a white dress & dark stockings & shoes; four of the others wear pompon-
trimmed dresses with pleated underskirts, & the remaining four wear
tunics and shorts.  1910-20; card 13.8 x 8.7 cm
10. sepia photographic postcard of a woman.  13.4 x 8.3 cm
11. sepia cabinet print (portrait proportions) by Horace H Dudley,
showing a little girl standing beside a young child who is seated on a
rustic bench: the girl's hair is tied with a ribbon & she wears a white pinafore, dark dress (with one leg of her drawers visible), & button boots; the child wears a white pinafore & dark dress with knee-socks & two-strap shoes.  1880-1900; image 13.3 x 9.3 cm
12. sepia photographic postcard of a woman.  Image 13.3 x 8.4 cm
13. sepia photographic postcard (portrait proportions) of a little boy
standing by a wooden bench: he wears a short-trousered sailor suit with button-boots.  1890-1910; card 13.3 x 8.5 cm
14. sepia photographic postcard of a young woman.  13.5 x 8.5 cm
15. sepia photographic postcard (landscape proportions) of a little girl with a bisque-headed open-mouthed baby doll in a pram; the girl's hair is cut in a fringed bob, and she wears a short, striped tunic dress with white socks and strap shoes.  1929-35; card 8.6 x 13.6 cm
16. sepia carte-de-visite by B G Brock of Northampton, showing the head
and shoulders of a youth in a suit with a white shirt and paisley-patterned tie.  1900-10; image 8.3 x 5.1 cm
17. black & white snapshot (portrait proportions) of two girls, both with fringed bobs, standing by railings with an arm around each other: the elder wears a two-tiered dress, T-strap sandals, & knee-socks with
check tops, & holds her panama hat by her side; the younger (possibly
the same child as in 15) wears a floral print dress, straw hat, white socks & strap shoes, & carries a handbag.  Inscribed on the reverse
"Agnes and Joan  1930".  Dated 1930; snapshot 8.9 x 6.3 cm
18. sepia carte-de-visite (portrait proportions) by R Roberts Willson
of Walworth, showing a little boy seated on top of a chair: he wears a
short-trousered sailor suit with matching hat, and ribbed hose with
lace-up boots.  1880-1900; carte 10.5 x 6.4 cm
19. sepia carte-de-visite (portrait proportions) by E Griffiths of Leicester, showing a little girl seated in a chair, half-length: her hair is cut in a fringe and she wears a tunic with a Swiss waistband. 1880-1900; carte 10.5 x 6.3 cm
20. sepia carte-de-visite (portrait proportions) by Grimmett of
Northampton, showing an adolescent girl standing by a canework chair,
half-length: she has a large bow in her shoulder-length hair, & wears
a yoked dress with a rope of pearls.  1890-1900; carte 10.5 x 6.5 cm
21. sepia carte-de-visite of a woman.  Carte 10.5 x 6.3 cm
22. sepia carte-de-visite of a young man in a suit.  10.6 x 6.3 cm
23. sepia photographic postcard of an army officer (cavalry/yeomanry
regt) of WW1.  Dated 1917; card 13.9 x 8.9 cm
24, 25. sepia photographic postcards of a young woman in a crepe dress, by Rotary Photos (24 Card 13.4 x 8.5 cm)(25 Card 13.7 x 8.5 cm)
26. sepia photographic postcard (portrait proportions) by Rotary Photo
of a woman & a little girl with their arms round each other: the girl has curly hair & wears a dress & sash.  1910-20; card 13.5 x 8.3 cm
27. sepia snapshot of a man in a back yard. Snapshot 8.6 x 6.2 cm
28. sepia snapshot of a woman inscribed "Mummie 1928" (possibly the
mother of the girls in 15,17).  Snapshot 8.7 x 6.1 cm
29. sepia snapshot (portrait proportions) of a little girl in a park or garden: she wears a caped coat, crocheted hat and white socks & shoes. 1920-25;snapshot 10.5 x 6.2 cm
30. sepia snapshot of a young woman kneeling under a tree & holding a
toddler who wears a silky frock & bonnet.  1920-25; 10.1 x 6.1 cm
31. sepia carte-de-visite of a young man.  Carte 10.5 x 6.3 cm
32. snapshot (landscape proportions) of three women, a man, a girl & a
boy sitting on an ornamental wall: the girl wears a cotton dress, beret,
ankle socks & lace-up shoes; the boy a jacket, long trousers, a soft-
collared shirt & lace-up shoes.  1925-35; snapshot 5.8 x 10.3 cm
33. snapshot (portrait proportions) of a woman & child paddling in the
sea: the child wears a short white dress.  1920-25; 10.1 x 6.2 cm
34. sepia cabinet print of a young man in army uniform.17.6 x 10.5 cm
35. sepia photographic postcard of a young woman.  Card 13.4 x 8.2 cm
36. sepia photographic postcard of a young woman.  Card 13.5 x 8.3 cm
37. sepia photographic postcard of the woman in (35).  13.5 x 8.3 cm
38. small sepia carte-de-visite print by Coldham & Son of Northampton,
showing a little boy in tweed knickerbockers, & a velvet jacket to which are pinned two prize medals. 1890-1910; carte 7.9 x 4 cm
39. small sepia carte-de-visite print by Coldham & Son of Northampton,
showing a little girl in a dark dress, to which two prize medals are pinned.  1890-1910; carte 7.8 x 4 cm
40. small sepia carte-de-visite print by Coldham & Son of Northampton,
showing a little boy in an Eton collar & a knickerbocker suit to which
two prize medals are pinned.  1890-1910; carte 7.8 x 4 cm
41. snapshot of a man.  Snapshot 6.9 x 4.3 cm
42. snapshot of a woman.  Snapshot 6.9 x 4.2 cm
43. snapshot of a girl with her hair "half-up", & wearing a lace-trimmed dress.  1905-15; snapshot 6.9 x 4.3 cm
44. snapshot of a man in a bowler hat. Snapshot 6.9 x 4.2 cm
45. snapshot of a man.  Snapshot 6.9 x 4.3 cm
fields.materials_techniques: (Album) tooled & gilt leatherette-bound boards & printed card pages; (images) photographic paper, some card-mounted
